    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-19T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-19T07:00:00-05:00" n="488"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4474: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-19T20:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1922—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 20—5:41 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>271. My 267, June 17, 1 p.m.<note n="56" xml:id="d488fn56">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_718">p. 718</ref>.</note>
                    Canton 16th and 17th, Sun with three gunboats raked bund with machine gun and
                    rapid fire. Two American buildings hit. Consul 18th protested to Sun at Whampoa
                    and Sun replied would again bombard but not bund unless fired on.</p>
                <p>Chen in Waichow and will remain there for the present. His nephew told consul two
                    gunboats willing to come over, also said forces sent to Shiuchow prevent troops
                    in Kiating [<hi rend="italic">Kiangsi?</hi>] coming to rescue.</p>
                <p>Have advised Admiral by wireless that American citizens and property may need
                    protection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
